{
  "stem": "14251.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But we soon found out, after a little bit of marching and this and that, that we found out two things-- that Russians drink like fish.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they were getting huge quantities of vodka just to be able to deal with what they had to deal with in the army.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Probably this is common in other countries, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "If there's a war, that's what you feed them-- cigarettes and vodka.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And the-- the other thing was that they consequently were drunk most of the hours that they were awake.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we would-- we would go on foot in the snow with people we didn't know, other German civilians that they were rounding up, and they would say, this is where we camp.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sometimes it was in the snow, and sometimes it was inside a place where the plates were still standing on the table where other people had left their meal.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that's how we came, among other places, to a place like Nemmersdorf.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember this terrible fear thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother would always-- whatever room-like thing we slept in-- and we were not with other people then-- bolting the door and putting a chair under the-- under the door handle and all this.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she always kept me exactly close to her.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nemmersdorf was still in East Prussia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- no, it was a village.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That village had-- there-- there had been a dispute whether the Germans had came in and had murdered all the Russians that had already captured the territory.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It went back and forth several times during the-- the months then and previous.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the other argument was that the Russians came in and murdered all the Germans who were in that town.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that whichever murdered whomever in it, the entire village was dead.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
